727671f-a.title: Queens: Parsons Boulevard - 72nd Avenue
727671f-a.text:
Parsons Boulevard, at the N.E. corner of 72nd Avenue,
showing two homes, the one on the right being of 18th century
construction and the one on the left being of recent timee.
The old house was the G. Van Dine (Van Dyks) property in
1873 and 1891 and was just north of Quarrelsome Lane, where
the old Jamaica Road bent westward around the Campbell and
Elflein farms.
P. L. Sperr  March 23, 1927
NO REPRODUCTIONS
